All Projects OF AFLF
1)	EDUCATION
Project VIDHYALAY: Illuminating Minds, Transforming Lives*

Welcome to Project “VIDHYALAY” At AFLF, we are committed to breaking the cycle of illiteracy and poverty by ensuring that every underprivileged child, every slum dweller, and every orphaned child has the opportunity to receive a quality education. Project Shiksha is our flagship initiative, dedicated to the cause of "Education for All."

*Our Mission for Project Vidhyalay:*

*Eliminating Child Labor:* We believe that no child should ever have to work to survive. Through Project Shiksha, we work tirelessly to eradicate child labor, providing these young souls with the gift of education.

*Access to Basic Education:* In India, illiteracy and poverty have kept countless children from accessing even the most basic education. Project Shiksha bridges this gap, offering a pathway to learning and empowerment.

*Empowering Women:* We recognize that education is not limited to children alone. We empower daily wage workers and school dropout women with basic education, giving them the ability to read, write, and sign their names, which can open doors to a brighter future.

*Our Impact:* Through Project Shiksha, we have witnessed the transformation of lives. We've seen children trade their work tools for books, slum communities embrace education as a beacon of hope, and women gaining the confidence to pursue better opportunities for themselves and their families.

*Join the Movement:* You can be a part of this transformative movement. Your support, whether through donations, volunteering, or advocacy, can help us bring education to those who need it most. Together, we can rewrite the stories of countless underprivileged children and marginalized women, ensuring that they have the chance to dream, learn, and succeed.

*Lighting the Path Forward:* Project Shiksha is not just about education; it's about empowerment. It's about equipping the most vulnerable with the tools they need to break free from the chains of poverty and illiteracy. Join AFLF in our mission to illuminate minds and transform lives, one child, one woman, and one community at a time.

2)	ZERO HUNGER DRIVE
Project Zero Hunger Drive - Ending Hunger Together

Welcome to Project “ZERO HUNGER DRIVE” The AFLF Project "Zero Hunger Drive" is dedicated to providing essential food to those who are in dire need, as countless individuals in Mumbai's slums and across India go without food, resulting in tragic hunger-related deaths. Our mission is to combat this issue through monthly food kit distributions. These kits contain items such as rice, wheat flour, rava, poha, oil, masala, and more, which are distributed to Below Poverty Line (BPL) families, senior citizens, Divyang members, visually impaired individuals, as well as those who are homeless and in need in Mumbai. Together, we can make a difference in the fight against hunger and malnutrition.
"There are miles to go before we AFLF sleep because in Mumbai's slums, many people are left hungry. We are hungry for change, and together, we can feed the hungry."
This powerful message underscores our dedication to combating hunger in Mumbai's slums and emphasizes the collective effort needed to make a difference in the lives of those who hunger for nourishment and change. Join us in our mission to provide food and hope to those in need.

3)	JAL PROJECT:
         Jal Project - Ensuring Access to Clean Drinking Water

Welcome to Project “JAL” In a world where clean drinking water is a basic necessity, the (AFLF) Ashray for Life Foundation is committed to making a difference through our dedicated project, "Jal."

Clean drinking water is not a luxury; it's a fundamental human right. Yet, many underprivileged communities in Mumbai, New Mumbai, and Thane face the daily struggle of accessing safe and clean water sources. This challenge not only affects their health but also their overall well-being.

"AFLF Project Jal" is our response to this critical need. Our mission is simple yet profound: to provide clean drinking water to underprivileged people in various locations across Mumbai, New Mumbai, and Thane. We believe that access to safe water is the cornerstone of good health, and it's a right that should be available to everyone, regardless of their circumstances.

Through "AFLF Project Jal," we are committed to installing clean water facilities, purifiers, and distribution points in areas where the need is most acute. We work tirelessly to ensure that no one in our community has to go without clean, fresh drinking water.

Clean water is the foundation of life, and together, we can make a significant impact. Join us in our mission to provide this essential resource to those who need it most. Your support can bring hope, health, and a brighter future to underprivileged communities across Mumbai, New Mumbai, and Thane.

If you share our passion for ensuring access to clean drinking water for all, we invite you to get involved. Your contributions, whether through donations or volunteering, can help us reach more people and create positive change in our communities.

Together, we can turn the tide and ensure that clean water flows freely to every corner of our city, improving the lives of countless individuals and families. Join AFLF Project Jal and be a part of this life-changing initiative.


